bsccm-jax — attribution and upstream copyrights
================================================

This project builds on the following BSD-3-Clause works. Their copyright notices
are retained here as required by that license.

1. BSCCM — Berkeley Single-Cell Computational Microscopy
   Copyright (c) 2022, monakhova (Waller Lab, UC Berkeley)
   https://github.com/Waller-Lab/BSCCM
   Paper: Pinkard, Liu, Nyatigo, Fletcher & Waller, "The Berkeley Single Cell
   Computational Microscopy (BSCCM) Dataset," arXiv:2402.06191 (2024).

   src/bsccm_jax/dpc.py is a derivative work: it re-implements in JAX the DPC
   weak-object transfer function forward model and Tikhonov phase reconstruction
   from bsccm/phase/functional_dpc.py. Method reference: Tian & Waller,
   "Quantitative differential phase contrast imaging in an LED array microscope,"
   Optics Express 23(9):11394 (2015), and its 2023 errata.

2. NSTM — Neural Space-Time Model
   Copyright (c) 2024, Ruiming Cao
   https://github.com/rmcao/nstm
   Paper: Cao et al., "Neural space-time model for dynamic multi-shot imaging,"
   Nature Methods (2024).

   src/bsccm_jax/neural_field.py is an INDEPENDENT re-implementation (Equinox +
   Optax) inspired by NSTM's neural-field object representation and coarse-to-fine
   annealed positional encoding. It is not a copy of NSTM's source and does not
   include NSTM's motion model or the `calcil`/`cc` training library.

This project is not a fork of either repository; both are used as a data source
and a methodological reference, respectively.
